 --At a meeting of the ministers of the Methodise Episcopal Church South, held in the office of the Richmond Christian Advests on the 19th inst, a Soldiers' Trust Society was formed, having in view the distribution of religions tracts and books among the soldiers of the Confederate army by  of  and those who may to engage in the week.

Large collections were obtained in several of the Methodise churches in this city on Sabbath last and a mass meeting will be held in furtherance of the objects of the Society, in the  Street Church, on Wednesday evening  seven o'clock. This meeting will be addressed by Hon. D. Clopton, Rev. C. K. Marshall, D. D., and others, and the public is  invited to attend.

